1. Encapsulation
2. Abstraction
3. Inheritance
4. Polymorphism
Normal Class:
    Blueprint
    Concrete function (normal functions with definition)
    Member variables (store data)

Abstract Class (cannot be instanstiated):
    Abstract function (function without definition)
    Concrete function
    
Polymorphism:
    Poly- many
    morph- forms
    ability to exist in many forms
Types: 
1. Function Overloading/ Static polymorphism/ Early binding
2. Function overriding/ Dynamic polymorphism/ late binding

Process of linking function calling with function definition - binding

Number of parameter or type of parameter or order of parameter:

import java.io.*;
import java.util.Scanner;
class first{
    void welcome(){
        System.out.println("Welcome Student Management System");
    }
    void welcome(String name){
        System.out.println("Welcome "+name);
    }
    public static void main(String args[]){
        first obj=new first();
        obj.welcome("ABC");
        obj.welcome();
    }
}

import java.io.*;
import java.util.Scanner;
class first{
    void welcome(){
        System.out.println("");
    }
    void welcome(String name, int roll) {
        System.out.println("Welcome " + name);
        System.out.println("Your Roll Number is " + roll);
    }
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        first obj = new first();
        obj.welcome("ABC", 1);
    }
}

Function overriding/method overriding: polymorphism
    existing class
    function definition
    runtime
    new class obj
    function update
    inheritance


import java.io.*;
import java.util.Scanner;
class program1{
    void fun1(){
        System.out.println("Old definition");
    }
}
class program2 extends program1{
    void fun1(){
        System.out.println("New definition");
    }
}
class first{
    public static void main(String args[]){
        program1 obj=new program1();
        obj.fun1();
    }
}

Write a program to design student management system, develop a function that stores user name
and display welcome message with student a function to store course details like course code and
duration now add a provision for a student to update or changing its course code but we want existing
details of course whenever required
*/

import java.io.*;
import java.util.Scanner;
class Student{
    String name;
    String courseCode;
    String duration;
    
    void welcomeStudent(String n) {
        name = n;
        System.out.println("Welcome " + name + " to Student Management System");
    }

    // function to store course details
    void setCourseDetails(String code, String dur) {
        courseCode = code;
        duration = dur;
    }

    // function to display course details
    void showCourseDetails() {
        System.out.println("Course Code: " + courseCode);
        System.out.println("Duration: " + duration);
    }

    // function to update course code
    void updateCourseCode(String newCode) {
        courseCode = newCode;
        System.out.println("Course Code updated successfully!");
    }
}

public class MainApp {
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        Student s = new Student();

        // input student name
        System.out.print("Enter Student Name: ");
        String name = sc.nextLine();
        s.welcomeStudent(name);

        // input course details
        System.out.print("Enter Course Code: ");
        String code = sc.nextLine();

        System.out.print("Enter Course Duration: ");
        String duration = sc.nextLine();

        s.setCourseDetails(code, duration);

        // display existing course details
        System.out.println("\nExisting Course Details:");
        s.showCourseDetails();

        // update course code
        System.out.print("\nEnter New Course Code to Update: ");
        String newCode = sc.nextLine();
        s.updateCourseCode(newCode);

        // display updated course details
        System.out.println("\nUpdated Course Details:");
        s.showCourseDetails();
    }
}
